ting norms"},"4":{"Display":"No clear norm"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID59"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6tZ9inq7UmTQyHk","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID6","SecondaryAttribute":"In this study, you will read a series of short scenarios. In each scenario, an individual faces s...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"In this study, you will read a series of short scenarios. In each scenario, an individual faces several possible actions. Your task is not to report what you personally would do. Instead, your goal is to <strong>indicate what you believe most other participants in this study will consider socially appropriate.<\/strong><br>\nBy socially appropriate, we mean behavior that most people would consider the <strong>correct or proper thing to do<\/strong> in that situation. Please read each scenario carefully and evaluate how socially appropriate each action is according to what you believe <strong>most other participants will think<\/strong>. Each action will be evaluated separately.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"General Instructions","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In this study, you will read a series of short scenarios. In each scenario, an individual faces s...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID6"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6tZ9inq7UmTQyHk","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID60","SecondaryAttribute":"Regarding the previous question","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Regarding the previous question","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidd